# Verification Checklist — Phase [N/TOTAL]

## Layer 1: Gates

- [ ] **EXIST**: All referenced files, functions, APIs verified to exist
- [ ] **RELEVANCE**: All changes are within phase plan scope
- [ ] **ROOT_CAUSE**: Fix addresses root cause, not symptom
- [ ] **RECALL**: Can articulate original constraints and IRON LAWS
- [ ] **MOMENTUM**: Making forward progress (write:read ratio reasonable)

## Layer 2: Self-Assessment

### BOUND Compliance
- [ ] No DANGER ZONE behavior changed without approval
- [ ] No NEVER DO rule violated
- [ ] All IRON LAWS verified:
  - [ ] [Iron Law 1]
  - [ ] [Iron Law 2]
  - [ ] [Iron Law 3]

### Tests
- [ ] All existing tests pass
- [ ] New tests added for new behavior
- [ ] Edge cases from MAP stage covered
- [ ] Test command: `[command]` → Result: [PASS/FAIL]

### Metrics
- [ ] Core metric: [value] — [stable/improved/regressed]
- [ ] No performance regression
- [ ] No increase in error rates

### Scope
- [ ] Changes within planned scope
- [ ] Out-of-scope changes documented: [none / list]
- [ ] No unintended side effects

## Layer 3: External Review

- [ ] Required? [Yes/No — based on complexity and BOUND interaction]
- [ ] If yes: user approval obtained

## Verdict

- [ ] **PASS** — advance to next phase
- [ ] **RETRY** — fix identified issue, re-verify
- [ ] **FAIL** — escalate to user

**Notes:** [any observations for the discovery log]
